The paper discusses the use of massive MIMO systems in cellular networks, which involves optimization of transmission using spatial degrees-of-freedom. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of low-cost hardware-constrained base stations, which involves system-level optimization and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large antenna arrays, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM).
